Militants in the Donbass fired from rocket-propelled grenades and mortars: 13 shells per day

02 Nov 2019, 05:21

The enemy fired at positions of the Ukrainian units from the forbidden weapon of the Minsk agreements
On Monday, November 1, fighters in Donbass 13 times violated the ceasefire regime.
The enemy fired on the positions of the units of the Joint Forces with the prohibited Minsk agreements of 120 mm mortars, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns and other small arms.
This is stated in the morning news release of the United Forces operation.
In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "East" the enemy carried out seven shellings:

twice near Starognatovka - 120 mm mortars, LNG and large machine guns;
near Talakivka - from small arms;
nearby Novognatovka - from anti-tank grenade launchers;
twice near the Water, which in the Azov region - with small arms and hand anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Marinka - with LNG and small arms.

In the area of responsibility of tactical group "North" the enemy carried out six shellings:

near Mayorsk - from anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Lugansk - from large machine guns and small arms and hand anti-tank grenade launchers;
twice near Novolugansky - with hand anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers and small arms;
near Free Farm - large caliber machine guns;
near Trinity - automatic grenade launchers.

Yesterday, November 1, there were no casualties as a result of firing by the Allied forces.
From the beginning of this day, the armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries did not show any fire activity.
As reported by Glavkom, on November 1, the stage of separation of forces and means on both sides was completed in Golden-4.
Recall, the withdrawal of forces and assets in the Gold began on October 29, despite statements about the shelling.
At the headquarters of the operations of the United forces stated that the process of separation of forces and assets near Golden-4 will take up to 30 days.
In the area of the Joint Forces operation, the order of the Joint Forces Commander has been introduced with yellow mode since October 28.
On November 1, the deployment of forces in Petrovsky was postponed due to shelling.
